  <div class="sections">
    <div class="inner-header">
      <h2>Journey Further With Our Unique Features</h2>
      <p>Embark is focussed on more than just contracts with out-of-the-box UI’s. We care about building powerful decentralized apps that will enable a more open and equitable web. Our tools now make it easy for more developers to build impactful products they can test and deploy simply and with confidence.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section section--odd section--one">
      <div class="section__text">
        <h2>Interactive Dashboard</h2>
        <div class="text">
          <p>Running Embark will reveal a dashboard right in your terminal that makes it easy to determine the state of your contracts, the environment you are using, and what Embark is doing, all at a glance. Even this part of</p>
          <p>Embark is configurable. Don’t like the dashboard? Just use embark run --nodashboard!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section__image">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section section--even section--two">
      <div class="section__text">
        <h2>Easy Configuration</h2>
        <div class="text">
          <p>Embark lets you manage complex systems of contracts easily, pass dynamic references to other contracts, deploy multiple instances, or access onDeploy or afterDeploy lifecycle hooks from with the same contracts.json file.</p>
          <p>Launch a blockchain of your own with one command. blockchain.json can be easily set up to start your specified environment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section__image">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section section--even section--three">
      <div class="section__text">
        <h2>Plugin Ecosystem</h2>
        <div class="text">
          <p>It’s all about extensibility. Use helpful pre-existing plugins for babel, webpack and a number of other JS build tools.</p>
          <p>Write your own plugins to suit your needs and share them with the whole community.</p>
          <p>Want to code in LLL? Use the LLL plugin. Want to support handlebars templates? Use the handlebars plugin. Want to develop DApps for Status easily? There’s a plugin for that.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section__image">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section section--even section--four">
      <div class="section__text">
        <h2>More Than Just a Blockchain Framework</h2>
        <div class="text">
          <p>In addition to the simple contracts.json file, Embark also comes with a storage.json and a communication.json file that allows you to connect with IPFS for storage and Whisper or Orbit for messaging. </p>
          <p>To deploy a dapp to IPFS, all you need to do is run a local IPFS node and then run `embark upload ipfs`. It really is that simple.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section__image">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
